# Build And Release Jar Workflow

When making code changes in this repository, always produce and archive a release jar.

## Build Command

Use this exact command:

```powershell
$env:JAVA_HOME='C:\Program Files\Java\jdk-21'; $env:Path="$env:JAVA_HOME\bin;$env:Path"; .\gradlew.bat :fabric:remapJar
```

## Copy To Releases

- Source jar: `fabric/build/libs/immersive_aircraft-<mc-version>.jar`
- Destination folder: `.releases/<mc-version>/`
- Naming format: `immersive_aircraft-<mc-version>-vNN-<change-summary>.jar`
- `vNN` must be the next version number already used in that destination folder.
- `<change-summary>` must be short kebab-case text describing the change.

Example:
- `immersive_aircraft-1.21.11-v47-advanced-pitch-smoothing-fix.jar`
